of Dowd serving as our Savior.

00:40:47.228 --> 00:40:50.871
And what I learned is that Dowd recognized that you read the opening chapter of the Towrah,

00:40:50.931 --> 00:40:52.733
Bare’shyth Genesis 1,

00:40:53.025 --> 00:40:54.585
and you realize that he is the greater luminary,

00:40:55.106 --> 00:40:57.246
he would have seen himself in that role serving as the sign of the Mow’edym.

00:40:57.365 --> 00:40:59.086
And he would have recognized the Mow’edym

00:40:59.387 --> 00:41:00.947
or Pesach, Matsah and Bikuwrym

00:41:01.004 --> 00:41:02.325
going through the last and Sukah.

00:41:02.865 --> 00:41:04.605
So he would have seen himself in that role.

00:41:05.610 --> 00:41:10.035
I’m convinced he probably also would have seen himself as the Tree of Lives

00:41:10.096 --> 00:41:10.635
in the second chapter of Genesis.

00:41:12.010 --> 00:41:14.452
He most certainly would have seen himself as ‘Eldad

00:41:16.112 --> 00:41:23.155
when Moshe failed with the children of Yisra’el,

00:41:23.235 --> 00:41:23.956
when they got to be too much for him.

00:41:23.976 --> 00:41:24.976
He would have seen himself as ‘Eldad,

00:41:25.597 --> 00:41:27.637
as Yahowah’s beloved.

00:41:27.639 --> 00:41:29.880
After all, his name was Dowd, and ‘Eldad means God’s beloved.

00:41:30.641 --> 00:41:31.922
He would have known that he was that prophet.

00:41:32.322 --> 00:41:34.043
He would have seen himself in the body of Yahowah,

00:41:36.844 --> 00:41:39.969
which is that magnificent ode to the future arrival of Dowd

00:41:40.030 --> 00:41:42.393
and all that would be accomplished with him.

00:41:42.498 --> 00:41:44.702
And he most certainly would have seen himself

00:41:45.926 --> 00:41:48.086
in the story of Abraham and Yitschaq climbing Mount Mowryah,

00:41:48.426 --> 00:41:51.467
when the discussion focuses on a father and son.

00:41:52.041 --> 00:41:53.302
And when Yahowah says,

00:41:53.782 --> 00:41:56.945
“I will provide the lamb” after a discussion on

00:41:56.985 --> 00:41:57.385
“don’t take the life of your son,

00:41:57.985 --> 00:41:58.385
your only son whom you love.”

00:41:58.672 --> 00:42:00.952
He would have immediately seen himself as Dowd

00:42:01.052 --> 00:42:04.436
because his name means beloved.

00:42:04.775 --> 00:42:06.976
And Yahowah had three times already said, he is my son.

00:42:07.318 --> 00:42:08.378
I am his father.

00:42:09.992 --> 00:42:12.556
And with the episode that transpired in 2 Samuel 6 and 7,

00:42:13.056 --> 00:42:14.739
where Yahowah speaks of bringing Dowd back in this magnificent way

00:42:15.278 --> 00:42:17.081
and reinforces that Dowd is in fact Yahowah’s beloved son,

00:42:18.068 --> 00:42:20.692
that he would have recognized that this is his role.

00:42:21.753 --> 00:42:23.539
He would have seen himself in this role.

00:42:24.572 --> 00:42:26.634
And then realizing how impossible it had been for him to lead Yisra’el.

00:42:26.643 --> 00:42:27.063
In fact,

00:42:27.123 --> 00:42:29.485
his own son led a coup against him.

00:42:30.264 --> 00:42:34.246
His wife besmirched his reputation, denied all the things that were pertinent about him.

00:42:34.425 --> 00:42:36.666
And he would have seen Moshe in the eleventh chapter of Bamidbar,

00:42:36.686 --> 00:42:38.565
giving up, saying, “God, just kill me

00:42:38.806 --> 00:42:41.306
because this job is impossible.

00:42:41.347 --> 00:42:45.108
These people cannot be led.

00:42:45.427 --> 00:42:46.827
It’s a miserable cast of characters.”

00:42:46.947 --> 00:42:48.369
He would recognize that God’s commitment

00:42:48.409 --> 00:42:48.869
to bring him back as king forevermore

00:42:48.889 --> 00:42:50.248
is a job that cannot be achieved

00:42:50.268 --> 00:42:51.268
unless something were to happen that was different.

00:42:51.731 --> 00:42:53.552
And Dowd realized, well,

00:42:53.972 --> 00:42:56.375
it’s my role to fulfill Pesach, Matsah, Bikuwrym.

00:42:56.643 --> 00:42:57.063
And if I do,

00:42:57.123 --> 00:42:59.485
every single one who will live forever with Yahowah,

00:42:59.505 --> 00:43:01.318
whom I will be king over, will be there because I made this sacrifice.

00:43:02.264 --> 00:43:04.246
He knew he would earn the respect of everyone.

00:43:06.068 --> 00:43:07.949
And so it was two days of suffering

00:43:07.989 --> 00:43:11.585
for an eternity of respect.

00:43:11.605 --> 00:43:14.146
It was the right call.

00:43:16.068 --> 00:43:17.949
And he knew he could trust Yahowah to pull it off with him.

00:43:17.989 --> 00:43:19.271
And he did.

00:43:19.811 --> 00:43:20.271
And so he went to Yahowah and said,

00:43:20.672 --> 00:43:24.175
“Obviously this is what you want and let’s do this together.”

00:43:24.757 --> 00:43:25.438
And Yahowah agreed.

00:43:25.478 --> 00:43:26.199
It was the right call.

00:43:28.161 --> 00:43:32.143
What greater way to establish his beloved son’s character and credibility

00:43:32.184 --> 00:43:35.485
than to accomplish all of this through him?

00:43:37.467 --> 00:43:43.130
And that’s how it all materialized.

00:43:43.210 --> 00:43:45.471
Now, as we return to this prior statement,

00:43:46.371 --> 00:43:48.152
I’m just on a technical point of view.

00:43:50.480 --> 00:43:51.081
‘Anah appeared in it,

00:43:51.101 --> 00:43:53.643
and it’s a very difficult word to translate

00:43:53.722 --> 00:43:57.364
because its root, chanan, mercy, does not work in the sentence.

00:43:57.405 --> 00:43:58.967
Further, it cannot be applied to Dowd in this context.

00:43:59.407 --> 00:43:59.706
So to better appreciate the meaning of ‘anah,

00:44:00.713 --> 00:44:03.394
we need to consider how it is used earliest in its debut in the Towrah.

00:44:03.918 --> 00:44:05.318
And there we find out that it is conveyed in a

00:44:07.394 --> 00:44:10.135
disproportionate amount of time in the Hitpa’el stem, which is rare.

00:44:10.396 --> 00:44:12.978
That’s where the speaker is acting on his own initiative,

00:44:13.478 --> 00:44:15.338
not being influenced by anyone else.

00:44:16.458 --> 00:44:17.498
And in these cases,

00:44:18.079 --> 00:44:22.041
‘Anah is an earnest plea by someone beseeching another for favor

00:44:22.101 --> 00:44:23.041
without any outside influence.

00:44:23.202 --> 00:44:25.802
It’s not providing a favor, but instead requesting one,

00:44:26.503 --> 00:44:27.083
which is why…

00:44:28.112 --> 00:44:30.652
I defined it as such in my translation of Mizmowr 6:9.

00:44:32.215 --> 00:44:35.056
So Dowd was requesting a chanan, a favor.

00:44:36.577 --> 00:44:37.317
In fact, two of them.

00:44:37.936 --> 00:44:40.438
One is he wanted the popular deceptions and religious delusions swirling around him silenced,

00:44:40.478 --> 00:44:42.559
so that his people could capitalize on his sacrifice.

00:44:43.340 --> 00:44:43.942
In addition,

00:44:44.262 --> 00:44:46.782
he wanted Yahowah to approve his request.

00:44:47.697 --> 00:44:49.056
Which was the most wonderful and terrifying decision ever made.

00:44:49.456 --> 00:44:51.338
He wanted the opportunity to serve as the Zarowah.

00:44:51.458 --> 00:44:59.382
It’s quite a request, isn’t it?

00:44:59.481 --> 00:45:01.242
And yet, there is still another challenge in this sentence.

00:45:02.275 --> 00:45:04.179
That one is overcoming a long history of religious corruption.

00:45:04.259 --> 00:45:05.460
In English Bibles, they render taphilah as prayer.

00:45:05.519 --> 00:45:06.440
Even though there is no basis for that connotation

00:45:06.900 --> 00:45:11.503
in the etymology of the word.

00:45:11.063 --> 00:45:11.965
It is either from palah or from palay.

00:45:12.552 --> 00:45:13.353
And it…

00:45:14.326 --> 00:45:19.010
It means to think and consider when and then to judge.

00:45:19.030 --> 00:45:19.771
So to exercise good judgment,

00:45:19.891 --> 00:45:21.913
which is to mediate then and request intervention.

00:45:24.059 --> 00:45:28.943
It speaks of what Dowd wanted to achieve for his people.

00:45:29.344 --> 00:45:29.945
And the best way to do it was to fulfill Chag Matsah.

00:45:31.672 --> 00:45:33.373
So lastly, the use of laqach,

00:45:33.753 --> 00:45:35.793
meaning to grasp, to receive, to accept, and to hold,

00:45:35.833 --> 00:45:36.373
is also a bit ill-fitting

00:45:36.954 --> 00:45:39.994
when viewed from the perspective of obtaining and holding someone in one’s hands.

00:45:40.056 --> 00:45:43.297
But it is perfectly suited to the idea of mentally embracing an idea

00:45:43.456 --> 00:45:47.338
of grasping its meaning and then accepting the potential that we can learn from this.

00:45:48.757 --> 00:45:50.938
So cognizant of these realities of the actual meaning of shama’,

00:45:51.039 --> 00:45:54.559
of takinah, of laqach, and taphilah,

00:45:55.621 --> 00:45:59.163
I think my translation not only differs markedly from the more popular renderings,

00:45:59.242 --> 00:46:02.423
but is vastly more meaningful.

00:46:03.463 --> 00:46:05.264
But what I always want to do is

00:46:05.347 --> 00:46:06.847
if my rendering of the words is different than the religious publications

00:46:06.985 --> 00:46:08.086
I want you to know why.

00:46:08.106 --> 00:46:09.911
I want you to be aware of my rationale

00:46:09.972 --> 00:46:12.574
and I want you to be able to do these same word studies

00:46:12.726 --> 00:46:14.329
to look at those four words and examine them

00:46:14.849 --> 00:46:15.550
as I have shared their etymological roots and first use meanings throughout the Towrah

00:46:16.414 --> 00:46:19.494
and examine them as I did.

00:46:20.655 --> 00:46:22.875
Approach this logically, systematically,

00:46:24.434 --> 00:46:29.675
and then be aware of the importance of laying everything upright

00:46:29.715 --> 00:46:33.137
so that everybody knows precisely the reasons that you have come to these conclusions,

00:46:33.637 --> 00:46:37.677
which is the unique aspect of my translations and also of my analysis on behalf of them.

00:46:37.697 --> 00:46:39.637
So here we find that the prime purveyor of forgiveness

00:46:39.677 --> 00:46:42.398
isn’t usually, well, in this case, is in an unusually unforgiving mood.

00:46:42.472 --> 00:46:44.974
So we should therefore view Dowd’s sacrifice as a divisive thing.

00:46:45.034 --> 00:46:48.998
It separates those for whom it was intended from those who would deny what he has accomplished,

00:46:49.039 --> 00:46:51.981
like the religious.

00:46:52.001 --> 00:46:53.724
Said another way, while Dowd perfected the children of the Covenant

00:46:53.744 --> 00:46:55.692
by taking our collective guilt into She’owl

00:46:55.731 --> 00:46:57.152
and depositing it there and never to be seen again,

00:46:57.192 --> 00:46:57.492
he also earned the right to determine She’owl’s future inmates.

00:46:57.913 --> 00:46:59.793
And as it would transpire,

00:47:00.152 --> 00:47:01.773
he is eager to humiliate those who disparaged his name,

00:47:02.458 --> 00:47:06.498
who dishonored his titles, who disdained and besmirched his accolades,

00:47:07.458 --> 00:47:10.681
who completely negated the value of his sacrifice for billions of people.

00:47:11.492 --> 00:47:15.635
And so this will be our last statement of this Mizmowr for today’s program.

00:47:15.695 --> 00:47:17.596
We’ll return to it as we open our program hopefully tomorrow,

00:47:17.616 --> 00:47:19.955
weather permitting.

00:47:19.974 --> 00:47:21.025
You can see it’s a little breezy here with the trade winds

00:47:21.025 --> 00:47:23.244
in the U.S. Virgin Islands.

00:47:23.264 --> 00:47:25.827
It reads:

00:47:26.150 --> 00:47:27.012
“All my enemies with animosity and rancor

00:47:27.072 --> 00:47:29.612
will be ashamed and they will be humiliated as a result of their own choices.

00:47:29.653 --> 00:47:30.813
They will have chosen their fate,

00:47:31.153 --> 00:47:34.275
which will be terrifying and agonizing beyond comprehension,

00:47:34.376 --> 00:47:35.097
receiving that which they have chosen to perpetrate.

00:47:35.817 --> 00:47:36.617
So once again,

00:47:36.717 --> 00:47:38.699
as a result of their own choices and having turned away,

00:47:38.719 --> 00:47:39.659
they will be held accountable for their shameful ambitions

00:47:40.119 --> 00:47:42.701
in an instant and continually thereafter.”

00:47:42.740 --> 00:47:48.083
Mizmowr, Lyrics to Sing, Psalm 6:10.

00:47:50.704 --> 00:47:50.925
You need to know that this is for keeps.

00:47:51.219 --> 00:47:54.380
You can choose to be religious or in the relationship or not at all.

00:47:54.400 --> 00:47:57.500
If you’re beguiled by religion, if you choose just to opt out for all of this,

00:47:57.520 --> 00:47:59.143
no hard feelings,

00:47:59.663 --> 00:48:00.722
your life ends like most do,

00:48:00.762 --> 00:48:02.222
and there is no reward, no punishment for you.

00:48:02.262 --> 00:48:05.123
Your soul simply ceases to exist.

00:48:05.164 --> 00:48:05.324
Fair.

00:48:06.889 --> 00:48:07.228
However,

00:48:07.289 --> 00:48:12.190
if you are demonstrating animosity and rancor towards Dowd

00:48:12.250 --> 00:48:17.210
by perpetrating identity theft through Christianity, Judaism, or Islam,

00:48:18.411 --> 00:48:19.552
that’s a different story.

00:48:20.492 --> 00:48:21.313
And so for those,

00:48:21.993 --> 00:48:22.873
they’re going to be ashamed.

00:48:22.893 --> 00:48:24.752
They will be humiliated because they’ve made this choice.

00:48:25.393 --> 00:48:27.275
The difference between omission and commission.

00:48:27.335 --> 00:48:27.815
Omission, you’ve been misled.

00:48:27.835 --> 00:48:29.547
So sorry for you.

00:48:29.588 --> 00:48:31.648
Commission, you are doing the misleading.

00:48:31.668 --> 00:48:33.530
You’re one of those people now on social media that is a keyboard evangelist

00:48:33.570 --> 00:48:37.333
promoting the stupidity of your religion that is based on the crime of identity theft.

00:48:37.838 --> 00:48:39.059
And that says they chose their fate.

00:48:39.518 --> 00:48:41.619
And their fate of the promoters of religion,

00:48:42.420 --> 00:48:44.983
of anti-Semitism, of anything that is opposed to what Dowd has achieved.

00:48:45.784 --> 00:48:46.324
They chose their fate.

00:48:46.344 --> 00:48:47.780
It’s going to be terrifying.

00:48:47.800 --> 00:48:49.282
It’s going to be agonizing.

00:48:49.362 --> 00:48:52.164
It’s going to be worse than you can comprehend to be incarcerated forever in a black hole.

00:48:52.204 --> 00:48:54.326
Because this is what they’ve chosen to perpetrate.

00:48:55.606 --> 00:48:58.070
We know that it is their choice because the niphal stem tells us

00:48:58.090 --> 00:48:58.911
that they carried this out

00:48:58.931 --> 00:49:00.025
and then brought the consequence upon themselves.

00:49:00.652 --> 00:49:02.335
The imperfect conjugation says that it will be enduring.

00:49:02.177 --> 00:49:03.699
And the jussive mood says that they chose it.

00:49:04.929 --> 00:49:05.528
Third person expression of volition.

00:49:05.588 --> 00:49:07.190
So once again, as a result of their own choices

00:49:07.230 --> 00:49:08.110
and having turned away,

00:49:08.150 --> 00:49:10.012
they will be held accountable for their shameful ambitions.

00:49:10.072 --> 00:49:15.635
You need to understand that we make our choices and we’re going to be held accountable.

00:49:15.695 --> 00:49:17.596
If God didn’t hold the religious, the anti-Semitic,

00:49:17.635 --> 00:49:18.036
the conspiratorial,

00:49:18.056 --> 00:49:19.677
and the overtly political, the militant accountable

00:49:19.697 --> 00:49:21.119
for all of the harm they have inflicted,

00:49:21.239 --> 00:49:22.780
then he wouldn’t be fair.

00:49:23.579 --> 00:49:25.561
And I can assure you who he’s going to.

00:49:25.601 --> 00:49:26.001
All of those people who have damaged Dowd’s reputation through religion,

00:49:26.581 --> 00:49:28.364
who have denied what he achieved through Christianity, Judaism, and Islam,

00:49:28.403 --> 00:49:30.425
and who have tormented God’s people through Marxism, communism, and conspiracy,

00:49:31.005 --> 00:49:33.867
you’re going to be held accountable.

00:49:34.492 --> 00:49:35.313
Your behavior was shameful.

00:49:37.554 --> 00:49:38.414
And this moment is going to occur in an instant,

00:49:38.434 --> 00:49:40.293
and then it will endure forevermore.

00:49:40.972 --> 00:49:44.635
We’re working towards that instant now.

00:49:45.536 --> 00:49:47.217
And that instant is on Taruw’ah.

00:49:49.101 --> 00:49:50.121
Right after the Taruw’ah harvest,

00:49:51.242 --> 00:49:52.364
at the dawn of Taruw’ah,

00:49:53.445 --> 00:49:55.025
right around six o’clock p.m. as the sun sets in Yeruwshalaim,

00:49:56.246 --> 00:49:57.447
the 23rd of September, 2033,

00:49:58.610 --> 00:49:59.831
many things are going to happen.

00:50:00.190 --> 00:50:03.012
And one of those is that everyone who has been opposed to Dowd,

00:50:03.356 --> 00:50:05.516
to Yisra’el, to Yahudim, to Yahowah,

00:50:06.257 --> 00:50:11.260
to the Towrah, to Yeruwshalaim, God’s people,

00:50:12.559 --> 00:50:14.820
particularly these plundering Muslims and Marxists.

00:50:14.860 --> 00:50:15.322
They’re going to be exterminated.

00:50:15.342 --> 00:50:16.403
It’ll happen in an instant.

00:50:17.324 --> 00:50:18.605
And everything that they have brought to bear against Yisra’el

00:50:18.644 --> 00:50:20.244
and all of the religious edifices will all be incinerated in an instant.

00:50:20.324 --> 00:50:21.605
And then they will be held accountable.

00:50:23.208 --> 00:50:24.769
And the accountability will be forever.

00:50:25.938 --> 00:50:26.960
You have been forewarned.

00:50:28.201 --> 00:50:28.420
Mizmowr,

00:50:28.460 --> 00:50:29.501
Lyrics to Sing.

00:50:30.202 --> 00:50:30.782
All of this,

00:50:31.603 --> 00:50:34.065
I’m sharing from the sixth psalm.

00:50:34.947 --> 00:50:35.726
I thank you for listening.

00:50:35.827 --> 00:50:38.028
We’ll resume in this place in our next program.

